Fitzgerald Memorial Field is a 3.11-acre iconic youth baseball diamond, located on the western bank of the Grand River, in the heart of downtown. Dedicated in 1936, the lighted and irrigated field now hosts the Mustang League baseball games (ages 9/10).

tags.description: The Dimondale Lion's Community Park, located at 304 West Jefferson Street, sits on the bank of the Grand River. The park offers a large pavilion, three picnic shelters, grills, restroom facilities, a natural fishing site, horseshoe pits and a playground.
tags.name: Dimondale Lions Community Park

tags.description: Oak Park is located on a northerly bluff overlooking the Grand River, offering 8.98 acres of quiet park space. A recent expansion of the park nearly doubled the size of the park which now offers nearly 1,180 feet of riverfront.
tags.name: Oak Park
